THE bomb squad and police have been called in to deal with an ongoing incident near a town centre.
Cordons have been put in place around the scene in the Castle Street area of Dunoon in Arygll and Bute.
Police said that inquiries are under way.
A Police Scotland spokesman said: “Police officers in Dunoon are dealing with an ongoing incident in the Castle Street area.
“Cordons have been put in place to allow the incident to be managed.”
